      <hedline>
        <hl1>Leaving Iraq To the Iraqis</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bob Corya letter holds that US got rid of Saddam Hussein, and now it should be up to Iraqis to run Iraq</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As I read ''Stop Bush's War,'' by Bob Herbert, and ''Rumsfeld's Blinkers,'' by David Brooks (columns, March 16), a thought occurred to me about Iraq.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>As I read ''Stop Bush's War,'' by Bob Herbert, and ''Rumsfeld's Blinkers,'' by David Brooks (columns, March 16), a thought occurred to me about Iraq.</p>
        <p>Suppose one night, say in May or June, every American soldier is put aboard a plane, along with as much war mat√©riel as practical, and flown from Iraq.</p>
        <p>Left behind in every city and town would be thousands of leaflets saying: ''We have gone home. We have given up on your fractured, broken, splintered nation. We got rid of your tyrant dictator; now it's up to you Iraqis to run Iraq. Good luck. Uncle Sam.''</p>
        <p>No more roadside explosions; no more dead Americans; and no more dead civilians caught up in the horrors of war. The tens of billions saved could be used for any number of worthwhile domestic projects.</p>
        <p>Bob Corya  Indianapolis, March 16, 2006</p>
      </block>
